"Powell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh: Anglicized form of Welsh <i>ap Hywel</i> ‘son of <i>Hywel</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘eminent’ (see   Howell  ).","Irish: mainly of Welsh origin as in 1 above, but sometimes a surname adopted as equivalent of Gaelic <b>Mac Giolla Phóil</b> ‘son of the servant of Saint Paul’ (see   Guilfoyle  ).","English: variant of   Paul   or   Poole  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Powel","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Powell  .","North German: from a form of the personal name   Paul  ."]},{"name":"Howell","meanings":["Welsh and English: in the Welsh border counties, from the Welsh male personal name <i>Hywel</i> ‘eminent’, popular since the Middle Ages particularly in honor of the great 10th-century law-giving Welsh king. The name may also arise from the Breton personal name <i>Houuel</i>, <i>Huwel</i>, <i>Huwal</i>, <i>Howael</i>, cognate with the Welsh name. Bretons were especially numerous in the eastern counties of England. See   Powell  .","English: perhaps from a Middle English personal name <i>Huwel</i> (spelled <i>Howel</i>), a shortening of <i>Huwelot</i> or <i>Huelin</i> (see   Hewlett   and   Huling  ), both pet forms of Middle English <i>Huw</i> (see   Hugh  ).","English: habitational name from Howell (Lincolnshire), from an uncertain initial element + Old English <i>wella</i> ‘well, spring, stream’."]},{"name":"Powles","meanings":["English and Welsh: variant of <b>Powells</b>, itself a variant of   Powell  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Roger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name, <i>Rog(i)er</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Roger Powell was born about 1338, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom as the son of Hywell Powell. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. Powell."},"et":{"about 1338–":"umbes 1338–Surnud","1338–Male":"1338–Surnud","1348–1363":"1348–1363","1334–1388":"1334–1388","1316–Male":"1316–Surnud","1316":"1316","1338":"1338","1348":"1348","about 1338":"umbes 1338","1334":"1334","1388":"1388","1363":"1363",", Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1338–":"noin 1338–Kuollut","1338–Male":"1338–Kuollut","1348–1363":"1348–1363","1334–1388":"1334–1388","1316–Male":"1316–Kuollut","1316":"1316","1338":"1338","1348":"1348","about 1338":"noin 1338","1334":"1334","1388":"1388","1363":"1363",", Somerset, England":"Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1338–":"environ 1338–Décédé","1338–Male":"1338–Décédé","1348–1363":"1348–1363","1334–1388":"1334–1388","1316–Male":"1316–Décédé","1316":"1316","1338":"1338","1348":"1348","about 1338":"environ 1338","1334":"1334","1388":"1388","1363":"1363",", Somerset, England":"Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Roger Powell est né environ 1338, à Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Hywell Powell. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs. Powell."},"de":{"about 1338–":"um 1338–Verstorben","1338–Male":"1338–Verstorben","1348–1363":"1348–1363","1334–1388":"1334–1388","1316–Male":"1316–Verstorben","1316":"1316","1338":"1338","1348":"1